# Trivy ignore file for the todo-app Helm chart.
# Each entry MUST have a justification. Re-review on every chart bump.

# AVD-KSV-0001 / KSV001: Process can elevate its own privileges.
#   Not ignored — the chart sets allowPrivilegeEscalation: false. Listed here
#   only as documentation that it is intentionally enforced, not suppressed.

# KSV011: CPU not limited.
#   Not ignored — resources.limits.cpu is set in values.yaml / values-prod.yaml.

# KSV014: Root file system is not read-only.
#   Not ignored — securityContext.readOnlyRootFilesystem: true is set, with a
#   writable emptyDir mounted at /tmp.

# --- Genuinely suppressed below ---

# KSV116: Runs with a default/empty seccomp profile on the DB-init Job.
#   The DB-init Job is a short-lived Helm hook (Atlas migrate apply) using the
#   upstream arigaio/atlas image; the pod-level seccompProfile RuntimeDefault
#   from podSecurityContext applies, but Trivy evaluates the hook Job in
#   isolation and can flag it. Accepted: ephemeral, no inbound traffic.
KSV116

# KSV104: Seccomp profiles disabled (image-level default on third-party image).
#   Applies to the arigaio/atlas migration image which we do not build. The
#   workload is namespaced, runs once per deploy, and drops ALL capabilities.
KSV104
